docs.abstract: Without evidence, President Trump asserted that some ballots in Florida “showed up out of nowhere” and that others were missing or forged.
docs.snippet: Without evidence, President Trump asserted that some ballots in Florida “showed up out of nowhere” and that others were missing or forged.
docs.lead_paragraph: For days, Mr. Trump has lobbed a series of misleading and baseless claims about the midterm election results in Florida. His latest missive about missing and forged ballots is no different.

headline.main: Trump Makes a Baseless Claim About ‘Massively Infected’ Ballots in Florida

docs.abstract: President Trump says the nuclear threat from North Korea is over. New satellite images of 16 hidden ballistic missile bases suggest that it has worsened since his summit meeting.
docs.snippet: President Trump says the nuclear threat from North Korea is over. New satellite images of 16 hidden ballistic missile bases suggest that it has worsened since his summit meeting.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — North Korea is moving ahead with its ballistic missile program at 16 hidden bases that have been identified in new commercial satellite images, a network long known to American intelligence agencies but left undiscussed as President Trump claims to have neutralized the North’s nuclear threat.

headline.main: In North Korea, Missile Bases Suggest a Great Deception
headline.print_headline: Hidden Bases In North Korea Suggest Deceit

docs.abstract: An explanation of legal dilemmas raised by the disclosure that the Justice Department has charged Julian Assange, the WikiLeaks founder, with a crime.
docs.snippet: An explanation of legal dilemmas raised by the disclosure that the Justice Department has charged Julian Assange, the WikiLeaks founder, with a crime.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The disclosure that federal prosecutors have brought an unidentified criminal charge against Julian Assange, the WikiLeaks leader, follows years of government deliberations over the dilemma raised by competing desires to put him out of business and fears that doing so could create a precedent that would undermine press freedoms.

headline.main: Julian Assange Charge Raises Fears About Press Freedom
headline.print_headline: The Complaint Is Murky, but the Risks to Press Freedom Are Clearer

docs.abstract: Mitch McConnell, who as majority leader controls the Senate floor, delivered the news in a meeting at the White House in which he told the president that the bill would eat up too much time.
docs.snippet: Mitch McConnell, who as majority leader controls the Senate floor, delivered the news in a meeting at the White House in which he told the president that the bill would eat up too much time.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Mitch McConnell told President Trump in a private meeting on Thursday that there is not likely to be enough time to bring a bipartisan criminal justice bill up for a vote this year, regardless of the support it has in the Senate and the White House, according to people familiar with the meeting.

headline.main: McConnell Tells Trump a Criminal Justice Bill Is Not Likely This Year
headline.print_headline: Trump-Backed and Bipartisan, but Mired in Senate

docs.abstract: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos unveiled sexual assault regulations for colleges and universities that bolster the rights of the accused.
docs.snippet: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos unveiled sexual assault regulations for colleges and universities that bolster the rights of the accused.
docs.lead_paragraph: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos unveiled a highly anticipated overhaul on Friday of the rules governing campus sexual assault, reducing the liability of colleges and universities for investigating sexual misconduct claims and bolstering the due process rights of defendants, including the right to cross-examine their accusers.

headline.main: Sex Assault Rules Under DeVos Bolster Defendants’ Rights and Ease College Liability
headline.print_headline: DeVos Unveils New Sex Assault Regulations Easing Colleges’ Liability

docs.abstract: President Trump told the special counsel that he knew of a project to build a Trump Tower in Moscow and discussed it with his longtime fixer before it fell apart, Mr. Trump’s lawyers said.
docs.snippet: President Trump told the special counsel that he knew of a project to build a Trump Tower in Moscow and discussed it with his longtime fixer before it fell apart, Mr. Trump’s lawyers said.
docs.lead_paragraph: The latest criminal charges against Michael D. Cohen, President Trump’s longtime fixer, for lying about a Moscow hotel deal raised questions of whether Mr. Cohen created new legal risks for Mr. Trump or his family members, possibly by contradicting what they told investigators about the same project.

headline.main: Trump’s Recall of Moscow Deal Matches Cohen’s, President’s Lawyers Say
headline.print_headline: Trump Says Cohen’s Story Matches His Own Account

docs.abstract: Nancy Pelosi gave her opponents a chance to cast a protest vote against her as she runs for House speaker, hoping that they would change course before a formal vote in January.
docs.snippet: Nancy Pelosi gave her opponents a chance to cast a protest vote against her as she runs for House speaker, hoping that they would change course before a formal vote in January.
docs.lead_paragraph: Going into a closed-door election among Democrats this week, Nancy Pelosi knew she had locked up support from the vast majority of her colleagues to become her party’s nominee for speaker of the House.

headline.main: Pelosi’s Strategy in Secret Ballot: Allow Her Critics to Let Off Steam
headline.print_headline: Allowing Protest Vote, Pelosi Will Now Try to Sway Skeptics
